Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: As you step onto the beaver dam, it breaks under your weight. The water from behind the dam washes everything downstream, including you. You have about given up hope when you find yourself washed ashore.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: something that looks suspiciously like a giant green blanket covering a large shape.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You step into the water, realizing too late that it is very deep and you cannot swim. Too bad!*018

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You try to hold the slippery moss but you cannot keep your grasp and fall down to the hard pathway. Too bad!*018

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: The Queen greets you with a kiss, thanks you for rescuing her, and gives you a gold crown!

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: The Queen greets you with joy, thanks you for getting rid of the giant, and gives you a crown of unfading flowers.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You can't make any sense of the words but as you read them you feel a strange sensation. When you stop reading you see the scroll is burning. You drop it quickly and watch it turn to ashes and the ashes blow away.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: As the dead spook sinks to the ground you see it turn to mist.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You have no trouble finding a horse that you, well, borrow to take you on your first adventure. You follow several signs which lead you to the Beginner's Forest.*010

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You see a green, vine covered arch with a locked wrought iron gate under the arch. Worked into the design of the gate are the words, "Beginners Only!"

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: You see Zeus Hightower Flabbergibungander, the local Forest Ranger, coming over to inspect you.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: He says, "You know, you really should have brought a weapon if you planned to adventure here! Come back when you are serious." He then walks away, shaking his head and muttering to himself.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: He shakes his head and says, "Who do you think you are fooling? You are clearly not a beginner and you shouldn't be here! Go back to the Main Hall."

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: Eventually he says, "You may proceed." He then unlocks the gate and walks away.

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: He tells you, "You may only take one weapon into the forest. Which shall it be?"

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: The ring you were wearing just vanished!

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: A bright light suddenly breaks through the cold blackness surrounding you. A tall wizard with a long gray beard appears in the light and starts waving a wand in your direction. He informs you that he works for the Eamon Commission **019

Simple.name: Desc
Simple.value: for the Fair Treatment of Characters and he is attempting to save you from the no-warning death trap that you just stumbled into. Everything starts to spin around you and suddenly you fall onto familiar ground. You are still alive!

Simple.value: A bright green glow envelops the blade of grass, then fades.
